Naaaaah!! \n< Serena >
Ohhh...Ugh. So this is the condition of Venus'
beauty...huh! \n< Man >
Ugh...groan...! \n< Serena >
I decided from the first glance. I decided when it was
presented by the Battbayar guy. \n< Man >
I will get you. \n< Man >
Someday, I'll do it like this...! Hmph!! \n< Man >
Aaah! \n< Serena >
Hahaha! It took five years but...! \n< Man >
Your place...it's better than I imagined! I'm never
gonna lose interest! My blood won't stop flowing! \n< Man >
Are all women from the northern region like this? \n< Man >
This battle is already coming to an end. Once the
grasslands become one, our next move will be to
rampage through the imperial territory... \n< Man >
It might be interesting to try invading the northern
area by passing through the large forest this time...
Huh! \n< Man >
Ah...ah...! Ughhh...! \n< Serena >
EJ... \n< Child >
Hey you all...! What are you doing, come back...! \n< Serena >
General, we have captured the brats of Batbayar. \n< Subordinate >
Good job. Hehehe. You all are quite ugly, not
resembling your mommy at all. Has the blood of
Batbayar come out strongly? \n< Man >
Hmm...We're one person short? Did we have some
insolent girl around here? \n< Man >
I'm sorry. She resisted. \n< Subordinate >
Ahhh...! \n< Serena >
I don't care if you didn't let them escape. \n< Man >
We're going to do the same thing anyway. \n< Man >
Very well. \n< Subordinate >
Stop it! \n< Serena >
Hmm? \n< Man >
P, please...! At least the children...! \n< Serena >
Did you create her willingly? The woman brought here
as a prize... \n< Man >
Children are innocent...All of them are good girls! \n< Serena >
The only shine I acquired in this captive life... \n< Serena >
...Why are you naked? What are you doing? And
who is that man? \n< Child >
T-This is...Mmm! Nothing...I have nothing at all...! \n< Serena >
EJ? Face, red... \n< Child >
It's okay, it's alri...ugh!...that's why...! \n< Serena >
Hmph. Even if they are just girls, at their age, it
would be better if they were a bit more observant. \n< Man >
It seems like the breed wasn't good. Or was it the
upbringing? You must have spoiled the cat. \n< Man >
Shut up...shut up! \n< Serena >
Don't worry. My seed is of better quality than
Batbayar's. I will soon make a replacement. A better
one at that. \n< Man >
If you're going to breastfeed anyway, wouldn't it be
better to have a strong child made from excellent
stock? \n< Man >
Take me along. \n< Man >
Eejiiiiiii!!! \n< Child >
Aaaaaaaaahhhhhhhhh!!!!! \n< Serena >
Here, don't cry, don't cry. This is also a custom of
troubled times. It is the fate of the grasslands. \n< Man >
Ow! \n< Serena >
A good woman has a duty, a responsibility to give
birth to a stronger child. \n< Man >
Leaving weak offspring is a sin against our ancestors. \n< Man >
How dare you...! How dare you...! Unbelievable...! \n< Serena >
Hahaha, yes, those eyes. The eyes of a mommy who has
had her child taken away. I wanted to see those eyes
of yours! \n< Man >
I'll quickly find a replacement. You just need to
keep bearing my children under my roof. \n< Man >
Hated boy My child's enemy, my child. \n< Man >
It's our child. They will grow up smart and strong.
And when they attack your hometown... \n< Man >
Doesn't your heart leap even when you just dream of
it? Hahaha, it's exciting. It's so exciting... \n< Man >
